This package uses the standard Unix software building method:

./configure
make
make install


configure is built with GNU autoconf and if you want modify it, you should
edit configure.ac instead and run autoreconf.

In addition to the standard autoconf settings --prefix, --bindir, etc
this package can be configured with various optional support packages, many
of which will be autodetected if no option is given. To see a list of all the
supported options and a description, run configure --help.